======================================================================
PART 7: STRAND COUPLING — HOW DELETION-CONTRACTION MIXES STRANDS
======================================================================

Fibonacci even/odd strand coupling:
  E_k = F_{2k}, O_k = F_{2k+1}
  k | E_k | O_k | 3E_{k-1}+O_{k-1} | E_{k-1}+2O_{k-1}
  1 |     1 |     2 | E_k = E+O =     1? True | O_k = E_k+O =     2? True
  2 |     3 |     5 | E_k = E+O =     3? True | O_k = E_k+O =     5? True
  3 |     8 |    13 | E_k = E+O =     8? True | O_k = E_k+O =    13? True
  4 |    21 |    34 | E_k = E+O =    21? True | O_k = E_k+O =    34? True
  5 |    55 |    89 | E_k = E+O =    55? True | O_k = E_k+O =    89? True
  6 |   144 |   233 | E_k = E+O =   144? True | O_k = E_k+O =   233? True
  7 |   377 |   610 | E_k = E+O =   377? True | O_k = E_k+O =   610? True
  8 |   987 |  1597 | E_k = E+O =   987? True | O_k = E_k+O =  1597? True
  9 |  2584 |  4181 | E_k = E+O =  2584? True | O_k = E_k+O =  4181? True

  Coupling matrix: (E_k, O_k)^T = M × (E_{k-1}, O_{k-1})^T
  where M = [[1, 1], [1, 2]]
  (because E_k = E_{k-1} + O_{k-1} and O_k = E_k + O_{k-1} = E_{k-1} + 2O_{k-1})
  Eigenvalues of M: [0.38196601 2.61803399]
  Product: 1.000000 (det = 1.000000)
  Sum: 3.000000 (trace = 3.000000)
  Note: eigenvalues = (3±√5)/2 = φ² and (1/φ)² = 2.618034 and 0.381966

Jacobsthal (x=2) even/odd strand coupling:
  E_k = J_{2k}, O_k = J_{2k+1}
  k=1: E=    1, O=    3 | E = O'+2E' =     1? True | O = E+2O' =     3? True
  k=2: E=    5, O=   11 | E = O'+2E' =     5? True | O = E+2O' =    11? True
  k=3: E=   21, O=   43 | E = O'+2E' =    21? True | O = E+2O' =    43? True
  k=4: E=   85, O=  171 | E = O'+2E' =    85? True | O = E+2O' =   171? True
  k=5: E=  341, O=  683 | E = O'+2E' =   341? True | O = E+2O' =   683? True
  k=6: E= 1365, O= 2731 | E = O'+2E' =  1365? True | O = E+2O' =  2731? True
  k=7: E= 5461, O=10923 | E = O'+2E' =  5461? True | O = E+2O' = 10923? True
  k=8: E=21845, O=43691 | E = O'+2E' = 21845? True | O = E+2O' = 43691? True
  k=9: E=87381, O=174763 | E = O'+2E' = 87381? True | O = E+2O' = 174763? True

  Coupling matrix at x=2: M_2 = [[2, 1], [2, 3]]
  Eigenvalues of M_2: [1. 4.]
  Product = 4.000000, Sum = 5.000000
  Note: eigenvalues = (5±√17)/2 ≈ 4.5616 and 0.4384
  Compare: at x=1, eigenvalues = φ² ≈ 2.6180 and 1/φ² ≈ 0.3820
  The 'tournament golden ratio' is (5+√17)/2 ≈ 4.561553

